<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Now that family and close friends are allowed in the NBA's Florida-based bubble, model Winnie Harlow wasted no time flying to see her beau Kyle Kuzma.</p>

<p>The 26-year-old Jamaican-Canadian beauty touched down at the Happiest Place on Earth on Monday after making sure last week that she was negative for the coronavirus.</p>

<p>Winnie and Kyle, who plays forward for the Los Angeles Lakers, have been dating since May and have been separated since the NBA restarted its 2020 season in Disney World. </p>

<p>Reunion: Now that family and close friends are allowed in the NBA's Florida-based bubble, model Winnie Harlow wasted no time flying to see her beau Kyle Kuzma and touched down in Orlando on Monday</p>

<p>Winnie traveled in style and flew on a swanky private jet to the NBA bubble in Orlando, Florida.</p>

<p>She documented her journey on social media, with the leggy beauty popping an exploding bottle of Veuve Clicquot Champagne mid-flight.</p>

<p>The stunner kept things casual but chic in a matching white sweatsuit with pink airbrushed designs.</p>

<p>Her hair was expertly styled in long locks and pulled into a half updo with face framing tendrils.</p>

<p>The good life: Winnie traveled in style and flew on a swanky private jet to the NBA bubble in Orlando, Florida</p>

<p>Long time: Winnie and Kyle, who plays forward for the Los Angeles Lakers, have been dating since May and have been separated since the NBA restarted its 2020 season in Disney World</p>

<p>Whoops: She documented her journey on social media, with the leggy beauty popping an exploding bottle of Veuve Clicquot Champagne mid-flight</p>

<p>Despite a long flight, Winnie looked fresh and glam when she arrived in Florida with shimmering silver eye shadow and long lashes.</p>

<p>On her Instagram Stories, the catwalker shared the breathtaking view from her hotel suite at Disney's Coronado Springs Resort.</p>

<p>Winnie is staying with her boyfriend who has been put up in the resort's Gran Destino Tower along with the rest of his team.</p>

<p>The Tower is not only home to the Lakers but the Los Angeles Clippers, the Miami Heat, the Milwaukee Bucks, the Toronto Raptors and the Boston Celtics.  </p>

